          <option value="mg/dL">mg/dL</option>
          <option value="mmol/L">mmol/L</option>
          <option value="%">%</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </div>
    <button class="btn-secondary" onclick="addCondEntry('diabetes')">Save reading</button>
    <div class="range-note">Typical reference points (labs vary): fasting glucose 70–99 mg/dL, post-meal under 140 mg/dL, HbA1c under 5.7%. Your doctor's personal target for you may differ — use these only as general context.</div>
    <div class="history-list" id="list-diabetes" style="margin-top:14px;"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- THYROID -->
  <div class="card cond-card cond-reveal thyroid" id="section-thyroid" style="display:none;">
    <span class="pill lavender" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Thyroid</span>
    <h2>Thyroid tracker</h2>
    <div class="sub">Both an underactive (hypothyroid) and overactive (hyperthyroid) thyroid can make periods heavier, lighter, irregular, or absent.</div>
    <div class="form-row">
      <div class="field">
        <label for="t-date">Test date</label>
        <input type="date" id="t-date">
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="t-type">Test</label>
        <select id="t-type">
          <option value="TSH">TSH</option>
          <option value="Free T4">Free T4</option>
          <option value="Free T3">Free T3</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="t-value">Value</label>
        <input type="number" id="t-value" placeholder="e.g. 2.5" step="0.01">
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="t-unit">Unit</label>
        <input type="text" id="t-unit" placeholder="e.g. mIU/L" value="mIU/L">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="form-row">
      <div class="field" style="flex:3;">
        <label for="t-symptoms">Symptoms today (optional)</label>
        <input type="text" id="t-symptoms" placeholder="e.g. fatigue, cold intolerance, hair thinning">
      </div>
    </div>
    <button class="btn-secondary" onclick="addCondEntry('thyroid')">Save reading</button>
    <div class="range-note">Typical adult TSH reference range is roughly 0.4–4.0 mIU/L, but exact ranges differ by lab and by whether you're being treated. Always read results with your doctor.</div>
    <div class="history-list" id="list-thyroid" style="margin-top:14px;"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ASTHMA -->
  <div class="card cond-card cond-reveal asthma" id="section-asthma" style="display:none;">
    <span class="pill sky" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Asthma</span>
    <h2>Asthma tracker</h2>
    <div class="sub">Hormone shifts across your cycle — especially right before your period — can make asthma symptoms flare for some people (sometimes called perimenstrual asthma).</div>
    <div class="form-row">
      <div class="field">
        <label for="a-date">Date</label>
        <input type="date" id="a-date">
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="a-peakflow">Peak flow (L/min, optional)</label>
        <input type="number" id="a-peakflow" placeholder="e.g. 420">
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="a-inhaler">Reliever inhaler uses today</label>
        <input type="number" id="a-inhaler" placeholder="e.g. 1" min="0">
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="a-severity">Symptom severity</label>
        <select id="a-severity">
          <option value="None">None</option>
          <option value="Mild">Mild</option>
          <option value="Moderate">Moderate</option>
          <option value="Severe">Severe</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </div>
    <button class="btn-secondary" onclick="addCondEntry('asthma')">Save entry</button>
    <div class="range-note">If you're needing your reliever inhaler much more than usual, having a peak flow drop of 20%+ from your personal best, or symptoms are severe, contact your doctor promptly rather than waiting to log it here.</div>
    <div class="history-list" id="list-asthma" style="margin-top:14px;"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- PCOS/PCOD GUIDANCE -->
  <div class="card cond-card cond-reveal" id="section-pcos" style="display:none;">
    <span class="pill" style="background:var(--pink-light); color:var(--pink-deep); margin-bottom:10px;">PCOS / PCOD</span>
    <h2>Understanding irregularity &amp; weight</h2>
    <div class="sub">PCOS (Polycystic Ovary Syndrome) and PCOD (Polycystic Ovarian Disease) are common hormonal conditions where cycles become irregular or unpredictable. Excess weight, particularly around the abdomen, can worsen insulin resistance, which in turn drives the hormonal imbalance — so weight and cycle irregularity often feed into each other.</div>

    <h3 style="font-size:15px; margin-bottom:10px;">Common signs worth noticing</h3>
    <div class="guide-grid" style="margin-top:0; margin-bottom:6px;">
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">01</span><h4>Irregular timing</h4><p>Cycles shorter than 21 days or longer than 35 days, or gaps of several months.</p></div>
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">02</span><h4>Unpredictable flow</h4><p>Very heavy, very light, or unpredictable bleeding from cycle to cycle.</p></div>
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">03</span><h4>Skin &amp; hair changes</h4><p>Acne, oily skin, hair thinning on the scalp, or extra hair growth on the face/body.</p></div>
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">04</span><h4>Weight changes</h4><p>Difficulty losing weight, or weight gain concentrated around the waist.</p></div>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size:15px; margin:22px 0 10px 0;">Steps that generally help manage it</h3>
    <div class="guide-grid">
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">01</span><h4>See a doctor first</h4><p>A gynecologist or endocrinologist can confirm what's happening with blood tests (hormones, insulin) and an ultrasound. Tracking data helps that conversation, but can't replace it.</p></div>
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">02</span><h4>Modest weight loss</h4><p>Losing even 5–10% of body weight is commonly reported to help restore more regular cycles by improving insulin sensitivity.</p></div>
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">03</span><h4>Lower glycemic-load eating</h4><p>Favoring whole grains, vegetables, legumes, and protein over refined carbs and sugar helps steady blood sugar and insulin levels.</p></div>
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">04</span><h4>Regular movement</h4><p>A mix of cardio and strength training several times a week is widely recommended for improving insulin sensitivity.</p></div>
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">05</span><h4>Sleep &amp; stress</h4><p>Poor sleep and chronic stress raise cortisol, which can worsen hormonal imbalance — consistent sleep and stress management support the rest.</p></div>
      <div class="guide-card"><span class="g-num">06</span><h4>Medical options</h4><p>Doctors sometimes prescribe hormonal birth control to regulate cycles, or medications like metformin for insulin resistance — these are prescription decisions, not self-directed ones.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="disclaimer">
    This app is an educational tracking tool, not a medical device. It cannot diagnose PCOS, PCOD, diabetes, thyroid disorders, asthma, or any other condition, and the reference ranges shown are general — not personalized targets. If your cycles are irregular, your readings look off, or something is worrying you, please see a doctor.
  </div>

  <footer>Your data is stored privately and only visible to you.</footer>
</div>

<script>
const KEYS = {
  entries: 'cycle-entries',
  settings: 'cycle-settings',
  diabetes: 'cond-diabetes',
  thyroid: 'cond-thyroid',
  asthma: 'cond-asthma',
  dailyLogs: 'daily-logs',
  themePref: 'theme-pref'
};

/* ---------- THEME ---------- */

function applyTheme(pref){
  let effective = pref;
  if(pref === 'system'){
    effective = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches ? 'dark' : 'light';
  }
  document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', effective);
}

function updateThemeButtons(pref){
  document.querySelectorAll('.theme-opt').forEach(btn=>{
    btn.classList.toggle('active', btn.getAttribute('data-pref') === pref);
  });
}

function setThemePref(pref){
  localStorage.setItem(KEYS.themePref, pref);
  applyTheme(pref);
  updateThemeButtons(pref);
  document.getElementById('themePanel').classList.remove('open');
}

function toggleThemePanel(){
  document.getElementById('themePanel').classList.toggle('open');
}

document.addEventListener('click', (e)=>{
  const panel = document.getElementById('themePanel');
  const fab = document.getElementById('themeFab');
  if(panel && !panel.contains(e.target) && e.target !== fab){
    panel.classList.remove('open');
  }
});

(function initTheme(){
  const pref = localStorage.getItem(KEYS.themePref) || 'system';
  applyTheme(pref);
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', ()=> updateThemeButtons(pref));
  if(window.matchMedia){
    window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').addEventListener('change', ()=>{
      const current = localStorage.getItem(KEYS.themePref) || 'system';
      if(current === 'system') applyTheme('system');
    });
  }
})();

/* Free up transform for hover transitions once entrance animations finish */
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', ()=>{
  document.querySelectorAll('.wrap > *, .hero-text, .mascot-box').forEach(el=>{
    el.addEventListener('animationend', function handler(){
      el.style.animation = 'none';
      el.removeEventListener('animationend', handler);
    });
  });
});

let entries = [];
let settings = {diabetes:false, thyroid:false, asthma:false, pcos:false};
let condData = {diabetes:[], thyroid:[], asthma:[]};
let dailyLogs = [];
let selectedMood = null;
let viewMonth = new Date(); viewMonth.setDate(1); viewMonth.setHours(0,0,0,0);
const LUTEAL_DEFAULT = 14;

function fmt(d){
  return d.toLocaleDateString('en-GB', {day:'2-digit', month:'short', year:'numeric'});
}
function parseDate(s){ return new Date(s + 'T00:00:00'); }
function daysBetween(a,b){ return Math.round((b-a)/86400000); }

async function safeGet(key){
  try{
    const raw = localStorage.getItem(key);
    return raw ? JSON.parse(raw) : null;
  }catch(e){ return null; }
}
async function safeSet(key, value){
  try{ localStorage.setItem(key, JSON.stringify(value)); }
  catch(e){ console.error('save failed', key, e); }
}

async function loadAll(){
  entries = (await safeGet(KEYS.entries)) || [];
  entries.sort((a,b)=> parseDate(a.start) - parseDate(b.start));

  const s = await safeGet(KEYS.settings);
  if(s) settings = Object.assign(settings, s);

  condData.diabetes = (await safeGet(KEYS.diabetes)) || [];
  condData.thyroid = (await safeGet(KEYS.thyroid)) || [];
  condData.asthma = (await safeGet(KEYS.asthma)) || [];
  dailyLogs = (await safeGet(KEYS.dailyLogs)) || [];

  const todayStr = new Date().toISOString().slice(0,10);
  const dlDateEl = document.getElementById('dl-date');
  if(dlDateEl && !dlDateEl.value) dlDateEl.value = todayStr;

  applySettingsToUI();
  setupMoodRow();
  render();
  renderAllConditions();
  renderCalendar();
  renderInsights();
}

function setupMoodRow(){
  document.querySelectorAll('.mood-opt').forEach(el=>{
    el.addEventListener('click', ()=>{
      const already = el.classList.contains('selected');
      document.querySelectorAll('.mood-opt').forEach(o=>o.classList.remove('selected'));
      if(!already){
        el.classList.add('selected');
        selectedMood = el.getAttribute('data-mood');
      } else {
        selectedMood = null;
      }
    });
  });
}

function applySettingsToUI(){
  ['diabetes','thyroid','asthma','pcos'].forEach(c=>{
    document.getElementById('chk-'+c).checked = !!settings[c];
    document.getElementById('chip-'+c).classList.toggle('active', !!settings[c]);
    const sec = document.getElementById('section-'+c);
    if(sec){
      if(settings[c]){
        sec.style.display = 'block';
        sec.classList.add('shown');
      } else {
        sec.style.display = 'none';
        sec.classList.remove('shown');
      }
    }
  });
}

function toggleCondition(name){
  settings[name] = document.getElementById('chk-'+name).checked;
  document.getElementById('chip-'+name).classList.toggle('active', settings[name]);
  const sec = document.getElementById('section-'+name);
  if(sec){
    if(settings[name]){
      sec.style.display = 'block';
      requestAnimationFrame(()=> requestAnimationFrame(()=> sec.classList.add('shown')));
      sec.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth', block:'nearest'});
    } else {
      sec.classList.remove('shown');
      setTimeout(()=>{ if(!sec.classList.contains('shown')) sec.style.display = 'none'; }, 300);
    }
  }
  safeSet(KEYS.settings, settings);
}

/* ---------- PERIOD ENTRIES ---------- */

function addEntry(){
  const start = document.getElementById('startDate').value;
  const end = document.getElementById('endDate').value;
  const flow = document.getElementById('flow').value;
  const notes = document.getElementById('notes').value;
  if(!start){
    document.getElementById('saveMsg').textContent = 'Please pick a start date.';
    document.getElementById('saveMsg').style.color = 'var(--alert)';
    return;
  }
  entries.push({start, end: end || null, flow: flow || null, notes: notes || null});
  entries.sort((a,b)=> parseDate(a.start) - parseDate(b.start));
  safeSet(KEYS.entries, entries);
  document.getElementById('startDate').value='';
  document.getElementById('endDate').value='';
  document.getElementById('flow').value='';
  document.getElementById('notes').value='';
  document.getElementById('saveMsg').textContent = 'Saved.';
  document.getElementById('saveMsg').style.color = 'var(--mint)';
  render();
  renderCalendar();
  renderInsights();
}

function deleteEntry(idx){
  entries.splice(idx,1);
  safeSet(KEYS.entries, entries);
  render();
  renderCalendar();
  renderInsights();
}

function getCycleLengths(){
  const lengths = [];
  for(let i=1;i<entries.length;i++){
    const len = daysBetween(parseDate(entries[i-1].start), parseDate(entries[i].start));
    if(len > 0 && len < 90) lengths.push(len);
  }
  return lengths;
}

function average(arr){ return arr.reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0) / arr.length; }
function stdDev(arr){
  if(arr.length < 2) return 0;
  const m = average(arr);
  const v = average(arr.map(x=>Math.pow(x-m,2)));
  return Math.sqrt(v);
}

function renderWheel(cycleDay, cycleLen){
  const svg = document.getElementById('wheelSvg');
  const cx=105, cy=105, r=90, thickness=20;
  const phases = [
    {name:'Menstrual', frac0:0, frac1:5/28, color:'#E0654F'},
    {name:'Follicular', frac0:5/28, frac1:13/28, color:'#E0A73B'},
    {name:'Ovulation', frac0:13/28, frac1:16/28, color:'#7FBF95'},
    {name:'Luteal', frac0:16/28, frac1:1, color:'#A98BC9'}
  ];
  function point(frac){
    const angle = (frac*360 - 90) * Math.PI/180;
    return [cx + r*Math.cos(angle), cy + r*Math.sin(angle)];
  }
  function arcPath(f0,f1){
    const [x0,y0] = point(f0);
    const [x1,y1] = point(f1);
    const large = (f1-f0) > 0.5 ? 1 : 0;
    return `M ${x0} ${y0} A ${r} ${r} 0 ${large} 1 ${x1} ${y1}`;
  }
  let svgContent = '';
  phases.forEach(p=>{
    svgContent += `<path d="${arcPath(p.frac0,p.frac1)}" stroke="${p.color}" stroke-width="${thickness}" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.95"/>`;
  });
  if(cycleDay !== null && cycleLen){
    const frac = Math.min(cycleDay / cycleLen, 0.999);
    const [mx,my] = point(frac);
    svgContent += `<circle cx="${mx}" cy="${my}" r="7" fill="#fff" stroke="#D6547A" stroke-width="3"/>`;
  }
  svg.innerHTML = svgContent;
}

function render(){
  renderStats();
  renderPredictions();
  renderHistory();
  renderAlert();
}

function renderStats(){
  const grid = document.getElementById('statGrid');
  const lengths = getCycleLengths();
  if(entries.length === 0){
    grid.innerHTML = `<div class="empty">Log your first period above to start seeing patterns.</div>`;
    document.getElementById('cycleDayNum').textContent = '–';
    document.getElementById('cycleDayLabel').textContent = 'no data yet';
    renderWheel(null, null);
    return;
  }
  const avgLen = lengths.length ? Math.round(average(lengths)) : null;
  const sd = lengths.length ? stdDev(lengths).toFixed(1) : '–';
  const lastStart = parseDate(entries[entries.length-1].start);
  const today = new Date(); today.setHours(0,0,0,0);
  const cycleDay = daysBetween(lastStart, today) + 1;

  grid.innerHTML = `
    <div class="stat"><span class="num">${entries.length}</span><span class="lbl">Periods logged</span></div>
    <div class="stat"><span class="num">${avgLen ? avgLen+'d' : '–'}</span><span class="lbl">Avg cycle length</span></div>
    <div class="stat"><span class="num">${sd}${sd!=='–' ? 'd':''}</span><span class="lbl">Variation (std dev)</span></div>
    <div class="stat"><span class="num">${cycleDay > 0 ? 'Day '+cycleDay : '–'}</span><span class="lbl">Current cycle day</span></div>
  `;
  document.getElementById('cycleDayNum').textContent = cycleDay > 0 ? cycleDay : '–';
  document.getElementById('cycleDayLabel').textContent = avgLen ? `of ~${avgLen}-day cycle` : 'need more data';
  renderWheel(cycleDay > 0 ? cycleDay : null, avgLen);
}

function renderPredictions(){
  const list = document.getElementById('predictList');
  if(entries.length === 0){
    list.innerHTML = `<div class="empty">Predictions appear once you've logged at least one period.</div>`;
    return;
  }
  const lengths = getCycleLengths();
  const avgLen = lengths.length ? Math.round(average(lengths)) : 28;
  const lastStart = parseDate(entries[entries.length-1].start);
  let html = '';
  for(let i=1;i<=3;i++){
    const predicted = new Date(lastStart);
    predicted.setDate(predicted.getDate() + avgLen*i);
    html += `
      <div class="predict-item">
        <span class="p-date">${fmt(predicted)}</span>
        <span class="p-tag">${i===1 ? 'Next period' : 'Month +'+i}</span>
      </div>`;
  }
  list.innerHTML = html;
  if(lengths.length === 0){
    list.innerHTML += `<div class="empty" style="margin-top:8px;">Based on a default 28-day estimate — log one more period for a personalized prediction.</div>`;
  }
}

function renderHistory(){
  const list = document.getElementById('historyList');
  if(entries.length === 0){
    list.innerHTML = `<div class="empty">No entries yet.</div>`;
    return;
  }
  const lengths = [];
  for(let i=1;i<entries.length;i++){
    lengths.push(daysBetween(parseDate(entries[i-1].start), parseDate(entries[i].start)));
  }
  let html = '';
  for(let i=entries.length-1; i>=0; i--){
    const e = entries[i];
    const lenText = i>0 ? `${lengths[i-1]} days since previous` : 'first logged entry';
    const endText = e.end ? ` – ${fmt(parseDate(e.end))}` : '';
    const flowText = e.flow ? ` · ${e.flow} flow` : '';
    html += `
      <div class="history-item">
        <div>
          <div class="h-dates">${fmt(parseDate(e.start))}${endText}</div>
          <div class="h-len">${lenText}${flowText}${e.notes ? ' · '+e.notes : ''}</div>
        </div>
        <button class="del-btn" onclick="deleteEntry(${i})">Remove</button>
      </div>`;
  }
  list.innerHTML = html;
}

function renderAlert(){
  const zone = document.getElementById('alertZone');
  const lengths = getCycleLengths();
  if(lengths.length < 2){ zone.innerHTML=''; return; }

  const sd = stdDev(lengths);
  const extremeCount = lengths.filter(l => l < 21 || l > 35).length;
  const irregular = sd > 7 || extremeCount >= 2;

  if(irregular){
    zone.innerHTML = `
      <div class="alert-banner">
        <h3>Your cycles look irregular</h3>
        <p>Based on your last ${lengths.length} logged cycles, the length has varied quite a bit (some cycles under 21 or over 35 days, or a lot of month-to-month swing). This pattern is sometimes linked to hormonal conditions like PCOS/PCOD, thyroid issues, or significant weight or stress changes. Turn on the relevant tracker below, and consider bringing this data to a doctor.</p>
      </div>`;
  } else {
    zone.innerHTML = '';
  }
}

/* ---------- CONDITION TRACKERS ---------- */

function addCondEntry(cond){
  let entry, key;
  if(cond === 'diabetes'){
    const date = document.getElementById('d-date').value;
    const type = document.getElementById('d-type').value;
    const value = document.getElementById('d-value').value;
    const unit = document.getElementById('d-unit').value;
    if(!date || value === '') return;
    entry = {date, type, value, unit};
    key = KEYS.diabetes;
  } else if(cond === 'thyroid'){
    const date = document.getElementById('t-date').value;
    const type = document.getElementById('t-type').value;
    const value = document.getElementById('t-value').value;
    const unit = document.getElementById('t-unit').value;
    const symptoms = document.getElementById('t-symptoms').value;
    if(!date || value === '') return;
    entry = {date, type, value, unit, symptoms: symptoms || null};
    key = KEYS.thyroid;
  } else if(cond === 'asthma'){
    const date = document.getElementById('a-date').value;
    const peakflow = document.getElementById('a-peakflow').value;
    const inhaler = document.getElementById('a-inhaler').value;
    const severity = document.getElementById('a-severity').value;
    if(!date) return;
    entry = {date, peakflow: peakflow || null, inhaler: inhaler || null, severity};
    key = KEYS.asthma;
  }
  condData[cond].push(entry);
  condData[cond].sort((a,b)=> parseDate(a.date) - parseDate(b.date));
  safeSet(key, condData[cond]);
  renderCondList(cond);
  clearCondForm(cond);
}

function clearCondForm(cond){
  if(cond==='diabetes'){ document.getElementById('d-value').value=''; }
  if(cond==='thyroid'){ document.getElementById('t-value').value=''; document.getElementById('t-symptoms').value=''; }
  if(cond==='asthma'){ document.getElementById('a-peakflow').value=''; document.getElementById('a-inhaler').value=''; }
}

function deleteCondEntry(cond, idx){
  const keyMap = {diabetes:KEYS.diabetes, thyroid:KEYS.thyroid, asthma:KEYS.asthma};
  condData[cond].splice(idx,1);
  safeSet(keyMap[cond], condData[cond]);
  renderCondList(cond);
}

function severityClass(sev){
  return 'severity-' + (sev||'none').toLowerCase();
}

function renderCondList(cond){
  const list = document.getElementById('list-'+cond);
  const data = condData[cond];
  if(!data || data.length === 0){
    list.innerHTML = `<div class="empty">No entries yet.</div>`;
    return;
  }
  let html = '';
  for(let i=data.length-1; i>=0; i--){
    const e = data[i];
    let line1='', line2='';
    if(cond==='diabetes'){
      line1 = `${fmt(parseDate(e.date))} · <span class="pill mint">${e.type}</span>`;
      line2 = `${e.value} ${e.unit}`;
    } else if(cond==='thyroid'){
      line1 = `${fmt(parseDate(e.date))} · <span class="pill lavender">${e.type}</span>`;
      line2 = `${e.value} ${e.unit}${e.symptoms ? ' · '+e.symptoms : ''}`;
    } else if(cond==='asthma'){
      line1 = `${fmt(parseDate(e.date))} · <span class="pill ${severityClass(e.severity)}">${e.severity}</span>`;
      const parts = [];
      if(e.peakflow) parts.push(e.peakflow+' L/min peak flow');
      if(e.inhaler) parts.push(e.inhaler+' inhaler use(s)');
      line2 = parts.join(' · ') || 'no measurements logged';
    }
    html += `
      <div class="history-item">
        <div>
          <div class="h-dates">${line1}</div>
          <div class="h-len">${line2}</div>
        </div>
        <button class="del-btn" onclick="deleteCondEntry('${cond}', ${i})">Remove</button>
      </div>`;
  }
  list.innerHTML = html;
}

function renderAllConditions(){
  renderCondList('diabetes');
  renderCondList('thyroid');
  renderCondList('asthma');
}

/* ---------- DAILY CHECK-IN ---------- */

function addDailyLog(){
  const date = document.getElementById('dl-date').value;
  if(!date){
    document.getElementById('dlMsg').textContent = 'Please pick a date.';
    document.getElementById('dlMsg').style.color = 'var(--alert)';
    return;
  }
  const sleep = document.getElementById('dl-sleep').value;
  const pain = document.getElementById('dl-pain').value;
  const discharge = document.getElementById('dl-discharge').value;
  const notes = document.getElementById('dl-notes').value;
  dailyLogs = dailyLogs.filter(l => l.date !== date); // one log per day, latest wins
  dailyLogs.push({date, mood: selectedMood, sleep: sleep || null, pain, discharge: discharge || null, notes: notes || null});
  dailyLogs.sort((a,b)=> parseDate(a.date) - parseDate(b.date));
  safeSet(KEYS.dailyLogs, dailyLogs);

  document.getElementById('dl-sleep').value='';
  document.getElementById('dl-discharge').value='';
  document.getElementById('dl-notes').value='';
  document.getElementById('dl-pain').value='None';
  document.querySelectorAll('.mood-opt').forEach(o=>o.classList.remove('selected'));
  selectedMood = null;
  document.getElementById('dlMsg').textContent = 'Saved.';
  document.getElementById('dlMsg').style.color = 'var(--mint)';

  renderCalendar();
  renderInsights();
}

/* ---------- OVULATION / FERTILE WINDOW ---------- */

function getOvulationWindow(){
  if(entries.length === 0) return null;
  const lengths = getCycleLengths();
  const avgLen = lengths.length ? Math.round(average(lengths)) : 28;
  const lastStart = parseDate(entries[entries.length-1].start);
  const nextPeriod = new Date(lastStart); nextPeriod.setDate(nextPeriod.getDate() + avgLen);
  const ovulation = new Date(nextPeriod); ovulation.setDate(ovulation.getDate() - LUTEAL_DEFAULT);
  const fertileStart = new Date(ovulation); fertileStart.setDate(fertileStart.getDate() - 5);
  const fertileEnd = new Date(ovulation); fertileEnd.setDate(fertileEnd.getDate() + 1);
  return {nextPeriod, ovulation, fertileStart, fertileEnd, avgLen};
}

function isWithin(date, start, end){
  return date >= start && date <= end;
}

/* ---------- CALENDAR ---------- */

function shiftMonth(delta){
  viewMonth.setMonth(viewMonth.getMonth() + delta);
  renderCalendar();
}
function goToday(){
  viewMonth = new Date(); viewMonth.setDate(1); viewMonth.setHours(0,0,0,0);
  renderCalendar();
}

function renderCalendar(){
  const label = document.getElementById('calMonthLabel');
  const grid = document.getElementById('calGrid');
  if(!label || !grid) return;

  label.textContent = viewMonth.toLocaleDateString('en-GB', {month:'long', year:'numeric'});

  const year = viewMonth.getFullYear();
  const month = viewMonth.getMonth();
  const firstDow = new Date(year, month, 1).getDay();
  const daysInMonth = new Date(year, month+1, 0).getDate();
  const today = new Date(); today.setHours(0,0,0,0);

  // Build lookup sets
  const periodDays = new Set();
  entries.forEach(e=>{
    const s = parseDate(e.start);
    const e2 = e.end ? parseDate(e.end) : new Date(s.getTime() + 4*86400000);
    for(let d = new Date(s); d <= e2; d.setDate(d.getDate()+1)){
      periodDays.add(d.toDateString());
    }
  });
  const logDays = new Set(dailyLogs.map(l => parseDate(l.date).toDateString()));

  const ov = getOvulationWindow();
  let predictedPeriodDays = new Set();
  let fertileDays = new Set();
  if(ov){
    for(let i=0;i<5;i++){
      const d = new Date(ov.nextPeriod); d.setDate(d.getDate()+i);
      predictedPeriodDays.add(d.toDateString());
    }
    for(let d = new Date(ov.fertileStart); d <= ov.fertileEnd; d.setDate(d.getDate()+1)){
      fertileDays.add(new Date(d).toDateString());
    }
  }

  let html = '';
  ['Su','Mo','Tu','We','Th','Fr','Sa'].forEach(d=> html += `<div class="cal-dow">${d}</div>`);
  for(let i=0;i<firstDow;i++) html += `<div class="cal-cell empty"></div>`;
  for(let day=1; day<=daysInMonth; day++){
    const d = new Date(year, month, day);
    const key = d.toDateString();
    let cls = 'cal-cell';
    if(periodDays.has(key)) cls += ' period';
    else if(predictedPeriodDays.has(key)) cls += ' predicted';
    else if(fertileDays.has(key)) cls += ' fertile';
    if(d.toDateString() === today.toDateString()) cls += ' today';
    const dot = logDays.has(key) ? '<span class="cal-dot"></span>' : '';
    html += `<div class="${cls}">${day}${dot}</div>`;
  }
  grid.innerHTML = html;

  // fertile window note under predictions
  const note = document.getElementById('fertileNote');
  if(note){
    if(ov){
      note.style.display = 'block';
      note.innerHTML = `🌱 Estimated fertile window: <b>${fmt(ov.fertileStart)} – ${fmt(ov.fertileEnd)}</b>, with estimated ovulation around <b>${fmt(ov.ovulation)}</b>. This assumes a typical ${LUTEAL_DEFAULT}-day luteal phase — it's a rough estimate, not a precise fertility method.`;
    } else {
      note.style.display = 'none';
    }
  }
}

/* ---------- INSIGHTS ---------- */

function renderInsights(){
  const container = document.getElementById('insightsList');
  if(!container) return;

  if(dailyLogs.length < 3){
    container.innerHTML = `<div class="empty">Log a few daily check-ins and patterns will start showing up here.</div>`;
    return;
  }

  const items = [];

  // Mood frequency
  const moodCounts = {};
  dailyLogs.forEach(l=>{ if(l.mood) moodCounts[l.mood] = (moodCounts[l.mood]||0)+1; });
  const topMood = Object.entries(moodCounts).sort((a,b)=>b[1]-a[1])[0];
  if(topMood){
    items.push({icon:'💗', text:`Your most logged mood is <b>${topMood[0]}</b> (${topMood[1]} of ${dailyLogs.length} check-ins).`});
  }

  // Pain vs pre-period window (last 5 days before a logged period start)
  if(entries.length >= 1){
    const preWindowDays = new Set();
    entries.forEach(e=>{
      const s = parseDate(e.start);
      for(let i=1;i<=5;i++){
        const d = new Date(s); d.setDate(d.getDate()-i);
        preWindowDays.add(d.toDateString());
      }
    });
    const preLogs = dailyLogs.filter(l => preWindowDays.has(parseDate(l.date).toDateString()));
    const painyPre = preLogs.filter(l => l.pain === 'Moderate' || l.pain === 'Severe').length;
    if(preLogs.length >= 3 && painyPre / preLogs.length >= 0.5){
      items.push({icon:'📈', text:`Moderate-to-severe pain shows up in <b>${painyPre} of ${preLogs.length}</b> check-ins from the 5 days before your period — a common PMS/PMDD pattern worth mentioning to a doctor if it's disruptive.`});
    }
    const irritablePre = preLogs.filter(l => l.mood === 'Irritable' || l.mood === 'Anxious' || l.mood === 'Sad').length;
    if(preLogs.length >= 3 && irritablePre / preLogs.length >= 0.5){
      items.push({icon:'🌙', text:`Lower moods (irritable, anxious, or sad) appear in <b>${irritablePre} of ${preLogs.length}</b> check-ins in the run-up to your period.`});
    }
  }

  // Average sleep
  const sleepVals = dailyLogs.map(l=>parseFloat(l.sleep)).filter(v=>!isNaN(v));
  if(sleepVals.length >= 3){
    const avgSleep = (average(sleepVals)).toFixed(1);
    items.push({icon:'😴', text:`You're averaging <b>${avgSleep} hours</b> of sleep across your logged check-ins.`});
  }

  if(items.length === 0){
    container.innerHTML = `<div class="empty">Keep logging — once there's more overlap between check-ins and periods, patterns will appear here.</div>`;
    return;
  }

  container.innerHTML = items.map(it => `
    <div class="insight-item">
      <span class="insight-icon">${it.icon}</span>
      <span class="insight-text">${it.text}</span>
    </div>`).join('');
}

loadAll();

if('serviceWorker' in navigator){
  window.addEventListener('load', ()=>{
    navigator.serviceWorker.register('service-worker.js').catch(()=>{ /* fine if unavailable, e.g. local file:// */ });
  });
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
